\lim_{n\rightarrow\infty}\int^\pi_{\frac{\pi}{2}}\frac{n\mathrm{sin}(\frac{x}{n})}{x}dx.
\frac{n\mathrm{sin}(\frac{x}{n})}{x}\rightarrow1
\sup_{x\in(\frac{\pi}{2},\pi)}\left|\frac{n\mathrm{sin}(\frac{x}{n})}{x}-1\right|.
x > \sin x > x-x^3/6
1 > \sin x/x > 1-x^2/6
0 < x < \pi/2
\lim_{t \to 0} \sin(t)/t = 1
